      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented evidence that simulation setup, boundary condition application, and post-processing were performed by qualified personnel following written procedures with independent review.",
      "rationale": "Use error was not assessed. No formal simulation execution procedure or independent review record was provided. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The choice of turbulence model, hemolysis constitutive model, and blood rheology model must be justified with sensitivity analysis demonstrating robustness of the hemolysis prediction.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty was not assessed. The power-law hemolysis model was selected without comparative evaluation against alternative formulations. Turbulence model sensitivity not reported. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Uncertainty in all model input parameters (geometry tolerances, fluid properties, boundary conditions) must be propagated through Monte Carlo analysis with documented parameter distributions.",
      "rationale": "Although Monte Carlo UQ was performed, input parameter distributions were assigned without experimental characterisation of geometry manufacturing tolerances or patient-specific fluid property variability. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
